commit.message:
Use proper format string specifier for size_t

On its help, the program uses the %ld format string specifier for size_t
values. This compiles fine for amd64, but causes FTBFS on i386.

This patch uses the %zu format string specifier to format size_t values.

Author: David da Silva Polverari <polverari@debian.org>
Signed-off-by: Artem Senichev <artemsen@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Avoid breaking the build on stricter build systems

Some builds, like Linux distro ones, may append -Wall to CFLAGS, causing
the build to break on any warning newer compilers' static analyzers
might include.

In some cases, like this one, the analyzer is not smart enough to verify
that msg is not user-controllable and thus not exploitable. Thus this
change is enough to make the compiler happy in any case.

Exclude Debian-specific menu system support

Pipewalker provides support for two menu systems: for the distro
specific Debian Menu System and for the Freedesktop Desktop Entry
Specification. As the Debian Technical Committee in 2015 has resolved
that they would migrate away from its own menu system towards the
Freedesktop one to avoid duplication [1], this support does not make
sense anymore.

[1] https://lists.debian.org/debian-devel-announce/2015/09/msg00000.html

Fix build system regarding FHS

According to the Filesystem Hierarchy Standard (FHS) 3.0 [1], on the
subsection 4.11.3, static data files for games should be installed on
${datarootdir}/games (same as ${PREFIX}/share/games).

[1] https://refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/FHS_3.0/fhs/ch04s11.html

Update configure.ac to a newer Autoconf

As configure.ac is making automake treat warnings as errors, builds
break on newer autotools versions. This commit is the result of running
autoupdate on the project.

Rename configure.in to configure.ac

The filename configure.in has been deprecated for a while in Automake.
Additionally, automake will eventually drop support for the deprecated
name, likely breaking non-compliant builds in the future (Closes #3).
